          "h": "Technical Details",
          "html": "MCU\nESP32-S3-WROOM-1-N16R8 — dual-core Xtensa LX7, 16 MB NOR flash, 8 MB PSRAM\nLogic Voltage\n3.3 V\nePaper Display\nGDEQ0213B74 — 2.13″, SPI (FSPI / SPI2), pins 5/6/7/15/16/17\nTFT Display\nST7735S — 1.8″, SPI (HSPI / SPI3), sprite-buffered rendering via TFT_eSPI\nKeyboard\nM5Stack CardKB V1.1 — full QWERTY, I²C at 5 V (address 0x5F)\nBoost Converter\nTPS613222ADBVR — battery voltage to +5 V synchronous boost; 2.2 µH inductor\nLDO Regulator\nXC6206P332MR-G — +5 V to +3.3 V for all logic peripherals\nBattery Charger\nTPB4056A20-ES1R — USB-C input, 5.1 kΩ CC resistors, single-cell LiPo\nLevel Shifting\n2× BSS138 N-FET bidirectional I²C shifter (SDA + SCL), 10 kΩ pull-ups each side\nLid Detection\nDRV5032FADBZR linear Hall effect switch + RC differentiator for rising-edge wake pulse\nBattery\n800 mAh LiPo\nPCB\n3.5″ × 2.0″, KiCad 9.0, full ground plane with antenna exclusion zone\nFramework\nArduino + FreeRTOS on PlatformIO\nPersistence\nESP32 NVS via Preferences library — up to 20 tasks, 50 calendar events"
